In any case, you can get at that function with base R methods:

{code}
> library(arrow)

Attaching package: ‘arrow’

The following object is masked from ‘package:utils’:

    timestamp

> get("create", ChunkedArray)
function (..., type = NULL) 
{
    if (!is.null(type)) {
        type <- as_type(type)
    }
    ChunkedArray__from_list(list2(...), type)
}
<environment: namespace:arrow>
{code}
